My programming team is working on a park function in our drive code for stabilization against defenders. We plan on setting all drive motors to zero and all the rotation motors set to 45 degrees. Every time we deploy with the new code the code fails. Is this the right direction to take for this function, or should this be done differently? The problems are caused by
ParkSub.java, and ParkCommand.java
Github: GitHub - polarrams/2025_2654 at 1-25-25-Park-Function
Any help would be awesome.
Thanks

You should have received a detailed error message with a stacktrace. Reading the stacktrace will tell you what the problem is.

In particular, it would tell you that your ParkSub Subsystem is trying to create a SparkMax with an ID that has already been created.

Using the built in YAGSL park function would be the right choice, but using this as an opportunity to learn about reading stacktraces will pay dividends in the future.
